{
  "texts": [
    "System OverviewTo capture the effect of user mobility and time-varying channel conditions, we adopt a time-slotted model that divides the offloading period into T slots with an equal duration τ.",
    "In this quasi-static setting, channel states and device parameters are assumed constant within a slot.",
    "Each mobile device m i generates a task per time slot, which is represented by a tuple We then define the association of mobile device m i to edge server e j using a binary decision variable.",
    "{d i, f M D i, f ES i },x ij = 1, if edge server j serves mobile device i, 0, otherwise.Each mobile device must offload its task to exactly one edge server, with no partial offloading allowed.",
    "Accordingly, the user association variable x ij is constrained byj∈E x ij = 1, x ij ∈ {0, 1}, ∀i ∈ M, j ∈ E(3) B. Communication ModelWe assume that the total network bandwidth W is equally divided among the E edge servers, such that each server e j is allocated with W j = W/E."
  ]
}